{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01DgNh2fkwEcumpVcdpj7fkz","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→# RNG Utopia - Scope\n     2→\n     3→Non-custodial P2P gaming platform on Solana, scoped for practical V1 execution.\n     4→\n     5→---\n     6→\n     7→## 1) Scope Goal\n     8→\n     9→Deliver a launchable V1 focused on:\n    10→- Two core games\n    11→- On-chain settlement\n    12→- Verifiable fairness\n    13→- Basic player history/profile\n    14→\n    15→This document defines what is in scope, out of scope, and deferred. It intentionally avoids implementation-level details.\n    16→\n    17→---\n    18→\n    19→## 2) Product Scope\n    20→\n    21→### In Scope (V1 Launch)\n    22→- Lord of the RNGs\n    23→- Coinflip\n    24→- Wallet connection (normal Solana wallet flow first)\n    25→- Non-custodial transaction flow for all financial actions\n    26→- Fairness verification experience for each game\n    27→- Basic user profile and history views\n    28→- Basic operational controls (pause/resume, monitoring, incident response)\n    29→\n    30→### Out of Scope (V1 Launch)\n    31→- Internal custodial balance model\n    32→- Multi-chain support\n    33→- Token launch and token utility\n    34→- Referrals/rakeback programs\n    35→- Lootboxes\n    36→- Profile customization/social linking\n    37→\n    38→### Deferred to V1.5 / V2\n    39→- Global chat\n    40→- Chat rewards\n    41→- Boss raids\n    42→- Deep quests system\n    43→- Advanced gamification loops\n    44→- Expanded social features\n    45→\n    46→---\n    47→\n    48→## 3) Architecture Direction (Locked)\n    49→\n    50→### Core Decisions\n    51→- Chain: Solana\n    52→- Custody: Non-custodial\n    53→- Program model: Standard Anchor programs (per-game + shared crate, see `docs/specs/004-shared-infrastructure/spec.md`)\n    54→- Wallet rollout: normal wallets first, embedded wallet expansion later\n    55→\n    56→### Explicit Constraint\n    57→- Do not build a temporary minimal program with planned rewrite.\n    58→- Continue on a single architecture path: program-per-game + shared Rust crate (`solana/shared/`). See pivot doc (`docs/pivot-doc.md`).\n    59→\n    60→---\n    61→\n    62→## 4) Source of Truth and Boundaries\n    63→\n    64→### On-Chain Source of Truth\n    65→- All money movement\n    66→- Round settlement outcomes\n    67→- Payout eligibility and claim state\n    68→\n    69→### Off-Chain Responsibilities\n    70→- Read models and indexing for UX/performance\n    71→- Basic profile/history aggregation\n    72→- Backend-assisted fairness services (secret generation, partial-sign create flows, settlement workers, verification endpoints)\n    73→- Fairness presentation and verification UX\n    74→- Real-time coordination where needed for UX\n    75→\n    76→### Rule\n    77→- If it changes user funds or determines payouts, it must be validated on-chain.\n    78→\n    79→---\n    80→\n    81→## 5) V1 Game Scope\n    82→\n    83→### Lord of the RNGs (V1)\n    84→- Multiplayer tier participation with multiple entries per player\n    85→- Backend-assisted hybrid fairness (commitment at create, public entropy capture at spin/start, automatic settlement)\n    86→- Round settlement with timeout-protected refund fallback\n    87→- Fairness verification path backed by public verification payloads and on-chain settlement evidence\n    88→\n    89→### Coinflip (V1)\n    90→- Match creation/join flow\n    91→- Backend-partially-signed create flow with wallet-authenticated requests\n    92→- Hybrid fairness outcome derived from revealed secret + future slot-hash entropy\n    93→- Automatic settlement with timeout-protected refund fallback\n    94→- Fairness verification path backed by public verification payloads and on-chain settlement evidence\n    95→\n    96→### Shared Game Requirements\n    97→- Idempotent action handling\n    98→- Replay protection for signed actions\n    99→- Clear error states for failed transactions\n   100→- Devnet-first validation before any production rollout\n   101→\n   102→---\n   103→\n   104→## 6) Functional Requirements (V1)\n   105→\n   106→- Users can connect wallets and perform game actions\n   107→- All financial interactions are on-chain\n   108→- Coinflip and Lord of the RNGs are playable end-to-end\n   109→- Users can verify fairness for completed rounds/matches\n   110→- Users can view basic profile and recent history\n   111→- Operators can pause/resume games\n   112→\n   113→---\n   114→\n   115→## 7) Non-Functional Requirements (V1)\n   116→\n   117→- Reliability: stable under expected early load\n   118→- Observability: errors and key events are visible\n   119→- Security baseline: rate limiting, validation, abuse protections\n   120→- UX baseline: clear transaction state feedback and recovery paths\n   121→- Operational readiness: incident checklist and rollback procedure\n   122→\n   123→---\n   124→\n   125→## 8) Delivery Plan\n   126→\n   127→### Phase 0 - Alignment and Readiness\n   128→- Confirm architecture decisions and provider selections\n   129→- Confirm game-level acceptance criteria\n   130→- Finalize launch scope freeze\n   131→\n   132→### Phase 1 - Coinflip End-to-End\n   133→- Complete real Coinflip game loop with backend-assisted create, automatic settlement, and on-chain payout verification\n   134→- Deliver fairness verification view for Coinflip\n   135→- Validate on devnet with end-to-end flows\n   136→\n   137→### Phase 2 - Lord of the RNGs End-to-End\n   138→- Complete real Lord of the RNGs game loop with backend-assisted fairness and on-chain payout verification\n   139→- Deliver fairness verification view for Lord of the RNGs\n   140→- Validate on devnet with end-to-end flows\n   141→\n   142→### Phase 3 - Profile/History + Ops Hardening\n   143→- Basic player profile/history from indexed data\n   144→- Operational controls, alerting, and runbook\n   145→- Stability pass and launch readiness checks\n   146→\n   147→### Phase 4 - Launch Gate\n   148→- Devnet validation complete\n   149→- Scope lock maintained\n   150→- No critical blockers remaining\n   151→\n   152→---\n   153→\n   154→## 9) Launch Readiness Checklist (V1)\n   155→\n   156→### Functional\n   157→- [ ] Wallet connection works for launch wallet path\n   158→- [ ] Lord of the RNGs playable end-to-end with real settlement path\n   159→- [ ] Coinflip playable end-to-end with real settlement path\n   160→- [ ] Fairness verification works for Lord of the RNGs\n   161→- [ ] Fairness verification works for Coinflip\n   162→- [ ] Basic profile/history available and accurate\n   163→\n   164→### Security and Integrity\n   165→- [ ] On-chain payout invariants validated\n   166→- [ ] Idempotency and replay protections validated\n   167→- [ ] Critical abuse paths mitigated\n   168→- [ ] Emergency pause tested\n   169→\n   170→### Operational\n   171→- [ ] Monitoring and error reporting active\n   172→- [ ] Incident and rollback playbook documented\n   173→- [ ] Devnet soak tests completed\n   174→\n   175→---\n   176→\n   177→## 10) Risks and Mitigations\n   178→\n   179→### Risk: Scope Expansion\n   180→- Mitigation: strict V1 boundary; defer social/gamification features\n   181→\n   182→### Risk: Multiplayer Jackpot Fairness Complexity\n   183→- Mitigation: isolate acceptance criteria for entry weighting, winner selection, backend settlement, and public verification early\n   184→\n   185→### Risk: First-Game Delivery Risk\n   186→- Mitigation: use Coinflip as first implementation target, then add Lord of the RNGs after core settlement and fairness flows are proven\n   187→\n   188→### Risk: Integration Drift from Existing Repo\n   189→- Mitigation: keep standard Anchor path (per-game + shared crate), avoid parallel architecture tracks\n   190→\n   191→### Risk: Wallet UX Friction\n   192→- Mitigation: ship stable normal wallet flow first; evaluate embedded wallet in V1.5\n   193→\n   194→---\n   195→\n   196→## 11) Success Metrics (V1)\n   197→\n   198→Primary:\n   199→- Successful completion rate of game rounds/matches\n   200→- Settlement correctness and claim success rate\n   201→- Fairness verification usage and pass rate\n   202→- Critical error rate within acceptable threshold\n   203→\n   204→Secondary:\n   205→- Early retention and repeat play behavior\n   206→- Time-to-complete for core game loop\n   207→\n   208→---\n   209→\n   210→## 12) Post-Launch Expansion\n   211→\n   212→### V1.5\n   213→- Chat (no rewards)\n   214→- Intro quests\n   215→- Simple points layer\n   216→- Embedded wallet rollout option\n   217→\n   218→### V2\n   219→- Chat rewards\n   220→- Boss raids\n   221→- Advanced quests and gamification depth\n   222→- Additional game(s)\n   223→- Referral system and broader social loops\n   224→\n   225→---\n   226→\n   227→## 13) Scope Governance\n   228→\n   229→- Any feature not listed under V1 In Scope is excluded by default.\n   230→- Deferred features require explicit re-prioritization after launch readiness review.\n   231→- Changes to custody model or architecture path require a separate decision memo.\n   232→\n   233→---\n   234→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"b0ecbf70-5847-4896-b164-b75514c07a62","uuid":"d670eea7-6d20-4008-889c-56c38bca4eb3","timestamp":"2026-03-19T21:49:30.158Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/workspaces/rng-utopia/docs/SCOPE.md","content":"# RNG Utopia - Scope\n\nNon-custodial P2P gaming platform on Solana, scoped for practical V1 execution.\n\n---\n\n## 1) Scope Goal\n\nDeliver a launchable V1 focused on:\n- Two core games\n- On-chain settlement\n- Verifiable fairness\n- Basic player history/profile\n\nThis document defines what is in scope, out of scope, and deferred. It intentionally avoids implementation-level details.\n\n---\n\n## 2) Product Scope\n\n### In Scope (V1 Launch)\n- Lord of the RNGs\n- Coinflip\n- Wallet connection (normal Solana wallet flow first)\n- Non-custodial transaction flow for all financial actions\n- Fairness verification experience for each game\n- Basic user profile and history views\n- Basic operational controls (pause/resume, monitoring, incident response)\n\n### Out of Scope (V1 Launch)\n- Internal custodial balance model\n- Multi-chain support\n- Token launch and token utility\n- Referrals/rakeback programs\n- Lootboxes\n- Profile customization/social linking\n\n### Deferred to V1.5 / V2\n- Global chat\n- Chat rewards\n- Boss raids\n- Deep quests system\n- Advanced gamification loops\n- Expanded social features\n\n---\n\n## 3) Architecture Direction (Locked)\n\n### Core Decisions\n- Chain: Solana\n- Custody: Non-custodial\n- Program model: Standard Anchor programs (per-game + shared crate, see `docs/specs/004-shared-infrastructure/spec.md`)\n- Wallet rollout: normal wallets first, embedded wallet expansion later\n\n### Explicit Constraint\n- Do not build a temporary minimal program with planned rewrite.\n- Continue on a single architecture path: program-per-game + shared Rust crate (`solana/shared/`). See pivot doc (`docs/pivot-doc.md`).\n\n---\n\n## 4) Source of Truth and Boundaries\n\n### On-Chain Source of Truth\n- All money movement\n- Round settlement outcomes\n- Payout eligibility and claim state\n\n### Off-Chain Responsibilities\n- Read models and indexing for UX/performance\n- Basic profile/history aggregation\n- Backend-assisted fairness services (secret generation, partial-sign create flows, settlement workers, verification endpoints)\n- Fairness presentation and verification UX\n- Real-time coordination where needed for UX\n\n### Rule\n- If it changes user funds or determines payouts, it must be validated on-chain.\n\n---\n\n## 5) V1 Game Scope\n\n### Lord of the RNGs (V1)\n- Multiplayer tier participation with multiple entries per player\n- Backend-assisted hybrid fairness (commitment at create, public entropy capture at spin/start, automatic settlement)\n- Round settlement with timeout-protected refund fallback\n- Fairness verification path backed by public verification payloads and on-chain settlement evidence\n\n### Coinflip (V1)\n- Match creation/join flow\n- Backend-partially-signed create flow with wallet-authenticated requests\n- Hybrid fairness outcome derived from revealed secret + future slot-hash entropy\n- Automatic settlement with timeout-protected refund fallback\n- Fairness verification path backed by public verification payloads and on-chain settlement evidence\n\n### Shared Game Requirements\n- Idempotent action handling\n- Replay protection for signed actions\n- Clear error states for failed transactions\n- Devnet-first validation before any production rollout\n\n---\n\n## 6) Functional Requirements (V1)\n\n- Users can connect wallets and perform game actions\n- All financial interactions are on-chain\n- Coinflip and Lord of the RNGs are playable end-to-end\n- Users can verify fairness for completed rounds/matches\n- Users can view basic profile and recent history\n- Operators can pause/resume games\n\n---\n\n## 7) Non-Functional Requirements (V1)\n\n- Reliability: stable under expected early load\n- Observability: errors and key events are visible\n- Security baseline: rate limiting, validation, abuse protections\n- UX baseline: clear transaction state feedback and recovery paths\n- Operational readiness: incident checklist and rollback procedure\n\n---\n\n## 8) Delivery Plan\n\n### Phase 0 - Alignment and Readiness\n- Confirm architecture decisions and provider selections\n- Confirm game-level acceptance criteria\n- Finalize launch scope freeze\n\n### Phase 1 - Coinflip End-to-End\n- Complete real Coinflip game loop with backend-assisted create, automatic settlement, and on-chain payout verification\n- Deliver fairness verification view for Coinflip\n- Validate on devnet with end-to-end flows\n\n### Phase 2 - Lord of the RNGs End-to-End\n- Complete real Lord of the RNGs game loop with backend-assisted fairness and on-chain payout verification\n- Deliver fairness verification view for Lord of the RNGs\n- Validate on devnet with end-to-end flows\n\n### Phase 3 - Profile/History + Ops Hardening\n- Basic player profile/history from indexed data\n- Operational controls, alerting, and runbook\n- Stability pass and launch readiness checks\n\n### Phase 4 - Launch Gate\n- Devnet validation complete\n- Scope lock maintained\n- No critical blockers remaining\n\n---\n\n## 9) Launch Readiness Checklist (V1)\n\n### Functional\n- [ ] Wallet connection works for launch wallet path\n- [ ] Lord of the RNGs playable end-to-end with real settlement path\n- [ ] Coinflip playable end-to-end with real settlement path\n- [ ] Fairness verification works for Lord of the RNGs\n- [ ] Fairness verification works for Coinflip\n- [ ] Basic profile/history available and accurate\n\n### Security and Integrity\n- [ ] On-chain payout invariants validated\n- [ ] Idempotency and replay protections validated\n- [ ] Critical abuse paths mitigated\n- [ ] Emergency pause tested\n\n### Operational\n- [ ] Monitoring and error reporting active\n- [ ] Incident and rollback playbook documented\n- [ ] Devnet soak tests completed\n\n---\n\n## 10) Risks and Mitigations\n\n### Risk: Scope Expansion\n- Mitigation: strict V1 boundary; defer social/gamification features\n\n### Risk: Multiplayer Jackpot Fairness Complexity\n- Mitigation: isolate acceptance criteria for entry weighting, winner selection, backend settlement, and public verification early\n\n### Risk: First-Game Delivery Risk\n- Mitigation: use Coinflip as first implementation target, then add Lord of the RNGs after core settlement and fairness flows are proven\n\n### Risk: Integration Drift from Existing Repo\n- Mitigation: keep standard Anchor path (per-game + shared crate), avoid parallel architecture tracks\n\n### Risk: Wallet UX Friction\n- Mitigation: ship stable normal wallet flow first; evaluate embedded wallet in V1.5\n\n---\n\n## 11) Success Metrics (V1)\n\nPrimary:\n- Successful completion rate of game rounds/matches\n- Settlement correctness and claim success rate\n- Fairness verification usage and pass rate\n- Critical error rate within acceptable threshold\n\nSecondary:\n- Early retention and repeat play behavior\n- Time-to-complete for core game loop\n\n---\n\n## 12) Post-Launch Expansion\n\n### V1.5\n- Chat (no rewards)\n- Intro quests\n- Simple points layer\n- Embedded wallet rollout option\n\n### V2\n- Chat rewards\n- Boss raids\n- Advanced quests and gamification depth\n- Additional game(s)\n- Referral system and broader social loops\n\n---\n\n## 13) Scope Governance\n\n- Any feature not listed under V1 In Scope is excluded by default.\n- Deferred features require explicit re-prioritization after launch readiness review.\n- Changes to custody model or architecture path require a separate decision memo.\n\n---\n","numLines":234,"startLine":1,"totalLines":234}}}
