{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01Y6hQ138njMcrbtGDY1z6VT","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! Now I have all the information I need. Let me compile the comprehensive inventory.\n\n## Backend Implementation Inventory for User-Profile/Transaction-History\n\n### 1. Migration File: User Transactions Table\n\n**File**: `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/services/backend/migrations/008_user_transactions.sql`\n\n**Lines 1-30**: Complete migration file. Schema overview:\n- **Table**: `user_transactions` (lines 7-16)\n  - Columns: `id` (BIGSERIAL, PK), `wallet` (TEXT NOT NULL), `game` (TEXT NOT NULL), `match_id` (TEXT NOT NULL), `event` (TEXT NOT NULL), `amount_lamports` (BIGINT NOT NULL), `tx_sig` (TEXT, nullable), `created_at` (TIMESTAMPTZ, default NOW())\n- **Indexes**: \n  - `idx_user_tx_wallet_created` (lines 19-20) — ON `(wallet, created_at DESC)` for pagination\n  - `idx_user_tx_match_id` (lines 23-24) — ON `(match_id)` for lookup\n- **Unique constraint** (lines 27-29): `uq_user_tx_wallet_match_event` — ON `(wallet, match_id, event)` for idempotency (ON CONFLICT DO NOTHING pattern)\n\n---\n\n### 2. DB Client Functions\n\n**File**: `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/services/backend/src/db.ts`\n\n**Types** (lines 101-124):\n- `UserTransactionEvent` type (line 104): \"join\" | \"win\" | \"loss\" | \"refund\"\n- `UserTransaction` interface (lines 106-115): shape including id, wallet, game, match_id, event, amount_lamports, tx_sig, created_at\n- `InsertUserTransactionParams` interface (lines 117-124): params for insertion (wallet, game, matchId, event, amountLamports, txSig?)\n\n**Function signatures** (lines 245-254):\n- `insertUserTransaction(params: InsertUserTransactionParams): Promise<void>` (line 246)\n- `getUserTransactions(wallet: string, cursor?: string, limit?: number, game?: string): Promise<UserTransaction[]>` (lines 249-254)\n\n**Implementation**:\n- `insertUserTransaction` (lines 533-546): Uses `ON CONFLICT DO NOTHING` for idempotency. No return value.\n- `getUserTransactions` (lines 548-584): Supports cursor pagination (keyed on `id`), limit clamping (max 50), and optional game filter. Returns rows in `id DESC` order (newest first).\n\n---\n\n### 3. Coinflip Write Paths\n\n#### 3a. Creator Join — POST /fairness/coinflip/create\n\n**File**: `/workspaces/rng-utopia/services/backend/src/routes/create.ts`\n\n**Lines 208-215**: Creator join transaction write\n```\nawait db.insertUserTransaction({\n  wallet: body.wallet,\n  game: \"coinflip\",\n  matchId: matchId.toString(\"hex\"),\n  event: \"join\",\n  amountLamports: body.amountLamports,\n});\n```\n- Called immediately after `insertRound` (line 174)\n- No `txSig` provided (will be null in DB)\n- No error handling — fire-and-forget\n\n#### 3b. Opponent Join — WebSocket PDA Watcher\n\n**File**: `/workspaces/rng-utopia/services/backend/src/worker/pda-watcher.ts`\n\n**Lines 120-132**: Opponent join transaction write (inside `handleCoinflipChange()`)\n```\ndb.insertUserTransaction({\n  wallet: match.opponent.toBase58(),\n  game: \"coinflip\",\n  matchId: Buffer.from(match.matchId).toString(\"hex\"),\n  event: \"join\",\n  amountLamports: Number(match.entryAmount),\n}).catch((err) => { ... });\n```\n- Triggered when match phase becomes PHASE_LOCKED (1) and server key matches\n- Called at line 121, fire-and-forget with error logging\n- No `txSig` provided\n\n#### 3c. Win/Loss on Settlement\n\n**File**: `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/services/backend/src/worker/settle-tx.ts`\n\n**Lines 304-323** (inside `settleMatch()` function):\n```\nconst loser = winner.equals(creator) ? opponent : creator;\nawait Promise.all([\n  db.insertUserTransaction({\n    wallet: winner.toBase58(),\n    game: \"coinflip\",\n    matchId: round.match_id,\n    event: \"win\",\n    amountLamports: payoutAmount,\n    txSig: txSignature,\n  }),\n  db.insertUserTransaction({\n    wallet: loser.toBase58(),\n    game: \"coinflip\",\n    matchId: round.match_id,\n    event: \"loss\",\n    amountLamports: Number(entryAmount),\n    txSig: txSignature,\n  }),\n]);\n```\n- Called at line 306 after round is transitioned to \"settled\" (line 282)\n- Includes `txSig` (settlement transaction signature)\n- Winner amount is `payoutAmount` (after fee deduction)\n- Loser amount is their original `entryAmount`\n\n---\n\n### 4. Lord of RNGs Write Paths\n\n**File**: `/workspaces/rng-utopia/services/backend/src/worker/settle-tx.ts`\n\n**Function**: `settleLordRound()` (lines 350-568)\n\n**Lines 518-543**: Win/loss transaction writes\n```\nconst userTxInserts = [\n  db.insertUserTransaction({\n    wallet: winner.toBase58(),\n    game: \"lord\",\n    matchId: round.match_id,\n    event: \"win\",\n    amountLamports: payoutAmount,\n    txSig: txSignature,\n  }),\n];\nfor (const entry of roundData.entries) {\n  if (!entry.player.equals(winner)) {\n    userTxInserts.push(\n      db.insertUserTransaction({\n        wallet: entry.player.toBase58(),\n        game: \"lord\",\n        matchId: round.match_id,\n        event: \"loss\",\n        amountLamports: Number(entry.amountLamports),\n        txSig: txSignature,\n      }),\n    );\n  }\n}\nawait Promise.all(userTxInserts);\n```\n- Called at line 543 after round is transitioned to \"settled\" (line 493)\n- Winner receives `payoutAmount` (after 3% fee)\n- Each losing entry records their original `amountLamports`\n- Note: Lord has NO join event writes (entries are stored on-chain in JSONB, not tracked per-player at time of entry)\n\n---\n\n### 5. Close Call Write Paths\n\n**File**: `/workspaces/rng-utopia/services/backend/src/worker/closecall-clock.ts`\n\n**Function**: `settleRound()` (lines 344-553)\n\n**Lines 489-538**: User transaction writes (after settlement TX confirmation)\n\nClose Call writes are done directly via `sql` template (postgres), not via `db.insertUserTransaction()`:\n\n```\nconst doInsert = (\n  wallet: string,\n  event: string,\n  amount: number,\n) =>\n  sql`\n    INSERT INTO user_transactions (wallet, game, match_id, event, amount_lamports, tx_sig)\n    VALUES (${wallet}, 'closecall', ${roundId}, ${event}, ${amount}, ${sig})\n    ON CONFLICT DO NOTHING\n  `;\n```\n\nFor each green entry (lines 506-519):\n- First: `doInsert(entry.player, \"join\", entry.amountLamports)`\n- If refund: `doInsert(entry.player, \"refund\", entry.amountLamports)`\n- If green won: `doInsert(entry.player, \"win\", payout)` where payout is share of `netPool`\n- If red won: `doInsert(entry.player, \"loss\", entry.amountLamports)`\n\nFor each red entry (lines 521-534): Similar pattern\n\n**Note**: Close Call write path uses raw SQL instead of `db.insertUserTransaction()` because it directly calls the postgres `sql` client (line 88, 166 passed as `db: postgres.Sql`). Uses the same ON CONFLICT DO NOTHING pattern.\n\n---\n\n### 6. API Route: Profile Transactions\n\n**File**: `/workspaces/rng-utopia/services/backend/src/routes/profile.ts`\n\n**Full file**: Lines 1-92\n\n**Route**: `GET /profile/transactions` (line 34)\n\n**Authentication** (lines 35-38): JWT middleware extracts wallet via `c.get(\"wallet\")`. Returns 401 if missing.\n\n**Query parameters** (lines 41-43):\n- `cursor` (optional): ID-based pagination cursor\n- `limit` (optional): page size\n- `game` (optional): filter by game\n\n**Game filtering** (lines 54-61): Maps both frontend names (e.g., \"lord-of-rngs\", \"close-call\") and DB names (e.g., \"lord\", \"closecall\") to canonical DB names via `TO_DB_GAME` map (lines 22-28).\n\n**Limit clamping** (lines 45-52): Parsed limit is clamped to max 50 (line 50).\n\n**Response shape** (lines 66-81):\n```json\n{\n  \"transactions\": [\n    {\n      \"id\": string,\n      \"game\": string (mapped to frontend name),\n      \"matchId\": string,\n      \"event\": \"join\" | \"win\" | \"loss\" | \"refund\",\n      \"amountLamports\": string (stringified),\n      \"txSig\": string | null,\n      \"createdAt\": ISO8601 timestamp\n    }\n  ],\n  \"nextCursor\": string | null\n}\n```\n\n**Pagination**: `nextCursor` is set to the last transaction's `id` if result count equals limit (line 77-78).\n\n---\n\n### 7. Price Endpoint\n\n**File**: `/workspaces/rng-utopia/services/backend/src/routes/price.ts`\n\n**Full file**: Lines 1-71\n\n**Route**: `GET /price/sol-usd` (line 57)\n\n**Dependency**: Pyth Hermes client\n- Feed ID: `SOL/USD` (lines 10-11): `0xef0d8b6fda2ceba41da15d4095d1da392a0d2f8ed0c6c7bc0f4cfac8c280b56d`\n- Endpoint: `https://hermes.pyth.network` (line 24)\n\n**Caching** (lines 26-52):\n- TTL: 60 seconds (line 13)\n- Cache miss → fetch latest from Hermes\n- Fetch error → return stale cache if available (line 50)\n\n**Response shape** (lines 62-66):\n```json\n{\n  \"price\": number (human-readable: base × 10^expo),\n  \"expo\": number (exponent, e.g., -8),\n  \"updatedAt\": ISO8601 timestamp (from Pyth publish_time)\n}\n```\n\n**Error**: Returns 503 if price unavailable and cache empty (line 60).\n\n---\n\n### 8. Route Registration\n\n**File**: `/workspaces/rng-utopia/services/backend/src/index.ts`\n\n**Profile routes** (lines 84-89):\n- Middleware: JWT auth on all methods (line 87)\n- Route: `app.route(\"/profile\", createProfileRoutes({ db }))` (line 89)\n\n**Price routes** (lines 189-190):\n- No middleware (public)\n- Route: `app.route(\"/price\", createPriceRoutes())` (line 190)\n\n---\n\n## Summary\n\n| Item | File | Lines | Key Details |\n|------|------|-------|-------------|\n| **Migration** | `008_user_transactions.sql` | 1-30 | Table schema, indexes, unique constraint on `(wallet, match_id, event)` |\n| **DB Types** | `db.ts` | 101-124 | `UserTransaction`, `InsertUserTransactionParams`, event enum |\n| **DB Insert** | `db.ts` | 533-546 | `insertUserTransaction()` with ON CONFLICT DO NOTHING |\n| **DB Query** | `db.ts` | 548-584 | `getUserTransactions()` with cursor, limit clamping (max 50), game filter |\n| **Coinflip Creator Join** | `routes/create.ts` | 208-215 | 