entry.player.toBase58(),\n        game: \"lord\",\n        matchId: round.match_id,\n        event: \"loss\",\n        amountLamports: Number(entry.amountLamports),\n        txSig: txSignature,\n      }),\n    );\n  }\n}\nawait Promise.all(userTxInserts);\n```\n- Called at line 543 after round is transitioned to \"settled\" (line 493)\n- Winner receives `payoutAmount` (after 3% fee)\n- Each losing entry records their original `amountLamports`\n- Note: Lord has NO join event writes (entries are stored on-chain in JSONB, not tracked per-player at time of entry)\n\n---\n\n### 5. Close Call Write Paths\n\n**File**: `/workspaces/rng-utopia/services/backend/src/worker/closecall-clock.ts`\n\n**Function**: `settleRound()` (lines 344-553)\n\n**Lines 489-538**: User transaction writes (after settlement TX confirmation)\n\nClose Call writes are done directly via `sql` template (postgres), not via `db.insertUserTransaction()`:\n\n```\nconst doInsert = (\n  wallet: string,\n  event: string,\n  amount: number,\n) =>\n  sql`\n    INSERT INTO user_transactions (wallet, game, match_id, event, amount_lamports, tx_sig)\n    VALUES (${wallet}, 'closecall', ${roundId}, ${event}, ${amount}, ${sig})\n    ON CONFLICT DO NOTHING\n  `;\n```\n\nFor each green entry (lines 506-519):\n- First: `doInsert(entry.player, \"join\", entry.amountLamports)`\n- If refund: `doInsert(entry.player, \"refund\", entry.amountLamports)`\n- If green won: `doInsert(entry.player, \"win\", payout)` where payout is share of `netPool`\n- If red won: `doInsert(entry.player, \"loss\", entry.amountLamports)`\n\nFor each red entry (lines 521-534): Similar pattern\n\n**Note**: Close Call write path uses raw SQL instead of `db.insertUserTransaction()` because it directly calls the postgres `sql` client (line 88, 166 passed as `db: postgres.Sql`). Uses the same ON CONFLICT DO NOTHING pattern.\n\n---\n\n### 6. API Route: Profile Transactions\n\n**File**: `/workspaces/rng-utopia/services/backend/src/routes/profile.ts`\n\n**Full file**: Lines 1-92\n\n**Route**: `GET /profile/transactions` (line 34)\n\n**Authentication** (lines 35-38): JWT middleware extracts wallet via `c.get(\"wallet\")`. Returns 401 if missing.\n\n**Query parameters** (lines 41-43):\n- `cursor` (optional): ID-based pagination cursor\n- `limit` (optional): page size\n- `game` (optional): filter by game\n\n**Game filtering** (lines 54-61): Maps both frontend names (e.g., \"lord-of-rngs\", \"close-call\") and DB names (e.g., \"lord\", \"closecall\") to canonical DB names via `TO_DB_GAME` map (lines 22-28).\n\n**Limit clamping** (lines 45-52): Parsed limit is clamped to max 50 (line 50).\n\n**Response shape** (lines 66-81):\n```json\n{\n  \"transactions\": [\n    {\n      \"id\": string,\n      \"game\": string (mapped to frontend name),\n      \"matchId\": string,\n      \"event\": \"join\" | \"win\" | \"loss\" | \"refund\",\n      \"amountLamports\": string (stringified),\n      \"txSig\": string | null,\n      \"createdAt\": ISO8601 timestamp\n    }\n  ],\n  \"nextCursor\": string | null\n}\n```\n\n**Pagination**: `nextCursor` is set to the last transaction's `id` if result count equals limit (line 77-78).\n\n---\n\n### 7. Price Endpoint\n\n**File**: `/workspaces/rng-utopia/services/backend/src/routes/price.ts`\n\n**Full file**: Lines 1-71\n\n**Route**: `GET /price/sol-usd` (line 57)\n\n**Dependency**: Pyth Hermes client\n- Feed ID: `SOL/USD` (lines 10-11): `0xef0d8b6fda2ceba41da15d4095d1da392a0d2f8ed0c6c7bc0f4cfac8c280b56d`\n- Endpoint: `https://hermes.pyth.network` (line 24)\n\n**Caching** (lines 26-52):\n- TTL: 60 seconds (line 13)\n- Cache miss → fetch latest from Hermes\n- Fetch error → return stale cache if available (line 50)\n\n**Response shape** (lines 62-66):\n```json\n{\n  \"price\": number (human-readable: base × 10^expo),\n  \"expo\": number (exponent, e.g., -8),\n  \"updatedAt\": ISO8601 timestamp (from Pyth publish_time)\n}\n```\n\n**Error**: Returns 503 if price unavailable and cache empty (line 60).\n\n---\n\n### 8. Route Registration\n\n**File**: `/workspaces/rng-utopia/services/backend/src/index.ts`\n\n**Profile routes** (lines 84-89):\n- Middleware: JWT auth on all methods (line 87)\n- Route: `app.route(\"/profile\", createProfileRoutes({ db }))` (line 89)\n\n**Price routes** (lines 189-190):\n- No middleware (public)\n- Route: `app.route(\"/price\", createPriceRoutes())` (line 190)\n\n---\n\n## Summary\n\n| Item | File | Lines | Key Details |\n|------|------|-------|-------------|\n| **Migration** | `008_user_transactions.sql` | 1-30 | Table schema, indexes, unique constraint on `(wallet, match_id, event)` |\n| **DB Types** | `db.ts` | 101-124 | `UserTransaction`, `InsertUserTransactionParams`, event enum |\n| **DB Insert** | `db.ts` | 533-546 | `insertUserTransaction()` with ON CONFLICT DO NOTHING |\n| **DB Query** | `db.ts` | 548-584 | `getUserTransactions()` with cursor, limit clamping (max 50), game filter |\n| **Coinflip Creator Join** | `routes/create.ts` | 208-215 | Fire-and-forget write, no txSig |\n| **Coinflip Opponent Join** | `worker/pda-watcher.ts` | 120-132 | WebSocket-triggered on PHASE_LOCKED |\n| **Coinflip Win/Loss** | `worker/settle-tx.ts` | 304-323 | Paired writes after settlement confirmed, includes txSig |\n| **Lord Win/Loss** | `worker/settle-tx.ts` | 518-543 | Winner gets payoutAmount, losers get entryAmount, includes txSig |\n| **Close Call Join/Win/Loss/Refund** | `worker/closecall-clock.ts` | 489-538 | Direct SQL writes (not via db client), per-entry granularity, includes txSig |\n| **Profile API** | `routes/profile.ts` | 34-89 | GET /transactions, JWT auth, cursor pagination, game filter, limit max 50 |\n| **Price API** | `routes/price.ts` | 57-70 | GET /sol-usd, Pyth Hermes, 60s cache, public |\n| **Route Registration** | `index.ts` | 84-90, 189-190 | Profile on `/profile` with JWT, Price on `/price` (public) |"}],"totalDurationMs":73809,"totalTokens":73866,"totalToolUseCount":26,"usage":{"input_tokens":3,"cache_creation_input_tok